  "text": "In the present study, [CITATION_1] investigated a potential role of altered miRNA biogenesis in ALS. To test this hypothesis, the authors took a comprehensive approach by combining the analysis of patient tissue, mouse models, and cell culture experiments. Expression profiling of motor neurons from patients by microarray revealed global downregulation of miRNAs in two distinct forms of ALS. This finding was recapitulated by inducing stress in a cell line using chemical stressors or overexpression of ALS-causing mutant genes. The authors observed reduction in several candidate miRNAs and concomitant premiRNA accumulation upon stress induction, as measured by qPCR. Together, these results represent a major advance compared to previous studies since they suggest defective miRNA biogenesis due to impaired Dicer processing as common denominator in ALS.",
